  "-- HANDBOOK EXTRA SECTIONS --": "-- HANDBOOK EXTRA SECTIONS --",

  "smoking-explanation-title": "Additional Mod Required",
  "smoking-explanation-text": "You can smoke bacon using the Smoking Rack from <a href=\"https://mods.vintagestory.at/butchering\">Butchering</a>.",
  "baconseed-handbook-title": "According to Legend...",
  "baconseed-handbook-text": "The mythical bacon crop was surprisingly robust, withstanding both extreme heat and extreme cold. It could grow in virtually any climate. Unfortunately, its benefits were evened out by its shortcomings, as the drop took nearly a full year to mature.",

  "-- HANDBOOK GUIDE --": "-- HANDBOOK GUIDE --",

  "baconbaconbacon-guide-title": "Bacon Bacon Bacon",
  "baconbaconbacon-guide-text": "<strong>Bacon Bacon Bacon</strong><br><i>A comprehensive guide to bacon production and preservation</i><br><br><strong>Obtaining Raw Bacon</strong><br>Raw bacon is harvested from <a href=\"handbooksearch://pig\">pigs</a>. When you harvest an adult pig, you'll find bacon alongside a decreased amount of redmeat. Word of warning: eating raw bacon will make you sick. Cook it first... unless want the Gourmand points.<br><br><strong>Cooking Your Bacon</strong><br>Toss your raw bacon into a <a href=\"handbooksearch://firepit\">firepit</a> or <a href=\"handbooksearch://clay oven\">clay oven</a> and let it sizzle. Cooked bacon is tender and delicious, but if you leave it a bit longer, you'll get perfectly crispy bacon with a satisfying crunch.<br><br><strong>Preservation Methods</strong><br>Bacon spoils like any meat, but you've got options:<br>• <i>Curing</i> - Seal raw bacon with <a href=\"handbooksearch://salt\">salt</a> in a <a href=\"handbooksearch://barrel\">barrel</a>. Cured bacon lasts an exceptionally long time and can be cooked for even better nutrition.<br>• <i>Smoking</i> - Requires the Smoking Rack from <a href=\"https://mods.vintagestory.at/butchering\">Butchering</a>. Gives your bacon a rich, smoky flavor.<br><br><strong>Processing & Pressing</strong><br>Cooked bacon can be pressed to extract <a href=\"handbooksearch://bacon grease\">bacon grease</a>, leaving behind a compressed brick of greasy bacon. Use a <a href=\"handbooksearch://knife\">knife</a> on pressed bacon to get dry cooked bacon - all the flavor without the heart palpitations. You can also press <a href=\"handbooksearch://lump of fat\">lumps of fat</a> right out of bacon grease by hammering it into oblivion.<br><br><strong>Bacon-Wrapped Meats</strong><br>Combining two strips of bacon with <a href=\"handbooksearch://redmeat\">redmeat</a>, <a href=\"handbooksearch://bushmeat\">bushmeat</a>, or <a href=\"handbooksearch://poultry\">poultry</a> will give you a protein powerhouse that provides the satiation of all three meats put together. Stews and soups have never filled your hunger bar so fast and still tasted so good. <br><br><strong>Booze Infusion</strong><br>For the adventurous: seal dry cooked bacon with a splash of <a href=\"handbooksearch://aqua vitae\">aqua vitae</a> in a barrel. The result is booze infused bacon. It'll get you a little tipsy, but don't knock it till you try it.<br><br><strong>Cooking With Bacon</strong><br>All bacon varieties work in <a href=\"handbooksearch://soup\">soups</a> and <a href=\"handbooksearch://stew\">meat stews</a>. You can even use bacon grease as a soup base. And yes, you can make an entire pie filled with bacon. You're welcome.<br><br><strong>Poultices</strong><br>In a pinch, bacon can even be used to dress wounds. Use a knife on raw or cured bacon to prepare a poultice and hold right-click to apply it. The cured variety works better, thanks to the salt. Just maybe don't leave raw pork on an open wound for too long.<br><br><strong>The Legendary Bacon Crop</strong><br><i>They say in ages past, there existed a plant that could grow bacon straight from the soil. The knowledge of its cultivation was lost to time, preserved only in cryptic rituals involving substances best left unspoken. Some claim the secret lies in the union of rendered fat and objects of peculiar significance - tokens wrapped in intoxicated meat, sealed away in vessels of grease. But surely, such tales are merely the ramblings of those who've had too much booze infused bacon...</i><br><br><i>Unless you or your server administrator turned it off</i>",

